ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: The type of immunotherapeutic related adverse event.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Paradoxical acceleration of tumor progression following the initiation of therapy.

Concepts.definition: Paradoxical acceleration of tumor progression following the initiation of therapy.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Inflammation of the muscle tissue of the heart.

Concepts.definition: Inflammation of the muscle tissue of the heart.
Inflammation of the colon.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Inflammation of the liver; usually from a viral infection, but sometimes from toxic agents.

Concepts.definition: Inflammation of the liver; usually from a viral infection, but sometimes from toxic agents.
Inflammation of renal tissue.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An inflammatory process affecting the skeletal muscles. Causes include infections, injuries, and autoimmune disorders.

Concepts.definition: An inflammatory process affecting the skeletal muscles. Causes include infections, injuries, and autoimmune disorders.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A disorder characterized by inflammation focally or diffusely affecting the lung parenchyma.

Concepts.definition: A disorder characterized by inflammation focally or diffusely affecting the lung parenchyma.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A disorder characterized by acute inflammation of the meninges of the brain and/or spinal cord.: Inflammation of the BRAIN due to infection, autoimmune processes, toxins, and other conditions. Viral infections (see ENCEPHALITIS, VIRAL) are a relatively frequent cause of this condition.

Concepts.definition: A disorder characterized by acute inflammation of the meninges of the brain and/or spinal cord.
An inflammatory process affecting the brain parenchyma. Causes include viral infections and less frequently bacterial infections, toxins, and immune-mediated processes.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An inflammatory process affecting the skin. Signs include red rash, itching, and blister formation. Representative examples are contact dermatitis, atopic dermatitis, and seborrheic dermatitis.

Concepts.definition: An inflammatory process affecting the skin. Signs include red rash, itching, and blister formation. Representative examples are contact dermatitis, atopic dermatitis, and seborrheic dermatitis.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the endocrine system. Representative examples of non-neoplastic disorders include diabetes mellitus, hyperthyroidism, and adrenal gland insufficiency. Representative examples of neoplastic disorders include carcinoid tumor, neuroendocrine carcinoma, and pheochromocytoma.

Concepts.definition: A non-neoplastic or neoplastic disorder that affects the endocrine system. Representative examples of non-neoplastic disorders include diabetes mellitus, hyperthyroidism, and adrenal gland insufficiency. Representative examples of neoplastic disorders include carcinoid tumor, neuroendocrine carcinoma, and pheochromocytoma.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A disorder affecting the cranial nerves or the peripheral nervous system.  It is manifested with pain, tingling, numbness, and muscle weakness.  It may be the result of physical injury, toxic substances, viral diseases, diabetes, renal failure, cancer, and drugs. -- 2004

Concepts.definition: A disorder affecting the cranial nerves or the peripheral nervous system. It manifests with pain, tingling, numbness, and muscle weakness. It may be the result of physical injury, toxic substances, viral diseases, diabetes, renal failure, cancer, and drugs.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Inflammatory and degenerative diseases of connective tissue structures, such as arthritis.

Concepts.definition: Inflammatory and degenerative diseases of connective tissue structures, such as arthritis.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Not occurring regularly or at short intervals.: The invasion of an organism's body tissues by disease-causing agents and their multiplication, as well as the reaction by the host to these organisms and/or toxins that the organisms produce.

Concepts.definition: Not occurring regularly or at short intervals.
The invasion of an organism's body tissues by disease-causing agents and their multiplication, as well as the reaction by the host to these organisms and/or toxins that the organisms produce.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

Concepts.definition: Different than the one(s) previously specified or mentioned.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Pertaining to or related to the blood and blood-forming organs.: A condition in which there is a lower-than-normal number of blood cells.

Concepts.definition: Pertaining to or related to the blood and blood-forming organs.
A laboratory test result indicating an abnormally low quantity of circulating blood cells.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The invasion of an organism's body tissues by disease-causing agents and their multiplication, as well as the reaction by the host to these organisms and/or toxins that the organisms produce.: A state of curiosity or concern about or attention to something.

Concepts.definition: The invasion of an organism's body tissues by disease-causing agents and their multiplication, as well as the reaction by the host to these organisms and/or toxins that the organisms produce.
A state of curiosity or concern about or attention to something.
